sec.p:
Many studies have revealed that the reactions of lead halide perovskites with H2O can accelerate the degradation process and deteriorate the chemical stability of PSCs [60, 61, 92]. In order to express the reaction mechanism more concisely, all chemical reactions of perovskite in this review are based on the archetypal MAPbI3 unless otherwise stated. Walsh et al. proposed the simple acid–base reversible reactions between MAPbI3 and H2O as follows [48], and a plausible decomposition pathway for MAPbI3 is shown in Fig. 2a.Fig. 2
