In addition, oxygen can also accelerate the aging of perovskite in humid conditions, which is attributed to the scavenging action of O2 on the H3O+ proton formed in the aforementioned deprotonation process (Eq. 2.1-12). The overall degradation reaction of MAPbI3 with the participation of O2 is shown as follows:2.1-14CH3NH3PbI3+14O2→H2O+TCPbI2+CH3NH2↑+12H2O+12I2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
