Unlike oxygen, light can induce the perovskites degradation without any presence of other environmental factors (e.g., water, oxygen). Study demonstrated that UV light can induce severe degradation of lead halide perovskites [108, 109]. As shown in Fig. 5a, Gao et al. detected Pb0 on the MAPbI3 surface after about 120 min of UV irradiation with a wavelength of 408 nm [110]. The proposed degradation reactions of MAPbI3 under UV irradiation can be generalized in Eqs. 2.1-34, 2.1-35. Figure 5b shows that the ratio of Pb0 remains nearly constant after 480 min of UV irradiation, which indicates that the decomposition of MAPbI3 has already saturated.Fig. 5
