Because of the intrinsic thermal instability of organic HTLs in normal PSCs, a lot of research efforts are devoted to inorganic HTLs [160–162], such as CuSCN, which is a promising candidate due to its low cost and durability [163–165]. It’s reported that the CuSCN can catalyze the thermal degradation process of perovskite films even in the absence of moisture and oxygen [82, 166–168], although the thermal stability of CuSCN itself is excellent. CH3NH3I and CuSCN can react to form CH3NH3SCN and CuI as follows:2.2-15CH3NH3PbI3+CuSCN→heatCuI+PbI2+CH3NH3SCN\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
